work cultures that recognize the value of varied perspectives. For me personally, engaging with these initiatives would mean not only advocating from within my professional circles but also using my platform as an accountant to speak out against stereotypes whenever I hear them. By addressing stereotype threat in STEM, we're not just working towards a more equitable field; we're also enriching our collective intellectual and creative potential. The journey to dismantle these barriers will be complex, fraught with challenges, but the payoff—a more inclusive, innovative, and dynamic STEM community—would be immeasurable.",
